20/09/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The defence ministry presented a programme Monday (19 September) for dealing with the surplus of army staff, as well as the social integration of personnel who lose their jobs. 
Some 800 officers will be out of work as a result of reforms in the military sector. 
According to the plan, they would be provided with assistance and professional training to help then adapt to civilian life. 
The programme is in line with NATO standards.
In other news, local police announced on Monday that 300kg of industrial explosives have been stolen from a private factory in the town of Bitola. 
The owner contacted police after noticing the material had disappeared. 
(Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax - 19/09/05)
